<item>
            <title>[SPARK-27070] DefaultPartitionCoalescer can lock up driver for hours</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27070</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re running Spark on EMR reading large datasets from S3. When trying to coalesce a&#160;UnionRDD of two large&#160;FileScanRDDs (each with a few million partitions)&#160;into around 8k partitions the driver can stall for over an hour.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Profiler shows that&#160;over 90% of the time is spent in TimSort which is invoked by `pickBin`. This seems like a very inefficient way to find the least occupied PartitionGroup. IMO a better way would just using the `min` method on the ArrayBuffer of `PartitionGroup`s&lt;/p&gt;</description>
